cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques, specifically using bidirectional recurrent neural networks to extract parallel sentences for improving machine translation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves deep learning techniques, which suggests it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with information retrieval and data sparsity, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the use of neural networks suggests it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
